01:19.621 --> 01:20.830
[GASPS]

01:20.914 --> 01:22.791
{\an3}PENNY.

01:23.041 --> 01:24.000
I CAN'T SEE, I CAN'T SEE,
MY GLASSES.

01:34.427 --> 01:35.220
[GASPS]

01:38.097 --> 01:40.016
OUT OF THE POOL... NOW.

01:40.266 --> 01:41.392
[GASPING]

01:41.476 --> 01:43.311
OH...

01:43.561 --> 01:45.730
[SCOFFS] NICE TANKINI.

01:49.567 --> 01:51.653
UH, PORTIA...

01:51.903 --> 01:54.197
{\an1}YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
STOP TALKING NOW.

01:54.447 --> 01:56.491
AW, ARE YOU "WOST"?

01:56.741 --> 01:58.451
THE KIDDY POOL'S THAT WAY.

01:58.701 --> 02:01.287
{\an1}HILARIOUS- GIVE HER
A HAND, MAUDE.

02:03.832 --> 02:05.416
[HEART THUMPING]

02:05.667 --> 02:06.960
[SCREAMING]

02:07.252 --> 02:09.044
[LAUGHS NERVOUSLY]

02:09.336 --> 02:12.674
{\an1}AW, MAN, THAT'S OUR PORTIA,
ALWAYS MAKING JOKES.

02:12.924 --> 02:14.884
{\an1}SHE'S A REGULAR
DON RICKLES, THAT ONE.

02:14.968 --> 02:16.803
{\an1}[WHISPERS]: Portia, can I
have a word with you, please?

02:17.137 --> 02:21.140
{\an3}UM, THAT WOULD MEAN ME
LISTENING TO YOU... SO NO.

02:21.391 --> 02:24.227
{\an1}DON'T YOU KNOW
WHO THOSE GIRLS ARE?

02:24.477 --> 02:25.895
THEY'RE THE FLIES.

02:25.979 --> 02:28.648
AS IN THE DRAGONFLIES.

02:28.898 --> 02:30.149
[BUZZING]

02:30.400 --> 02:31.734
AND WE LIKE USING YOUR POOL.

02:31.985 --> 02:34.571
WITHOUT YOU IN IT, SO GO.

02:34.821 --> 02:38.658
I'M SORRY, THAT PINK IS SO LOUD,
I COULDN'T HEAR YOU.

02:41.035 --> 02:43.746
{\an1}LISTEN, THERE'S PLENTY OF ROOM
IN THE POOL FOR EVERYONE.

02:43.997 --> 02:46.249
{\an1}WHY DON'T YOU PUT ON YOUR
FLOATIES AND WE CAN ALL SHARE?

02:46.499 --> 02:47.584
THAT SOUNDS LIKE...

02:47.834 --> 02:50.378
[LAUGHING]

02:50.628 --> 02:52.380
NO, THANKS.

02:52.630 --> 02:54.048
WE GAVE YOU A CHANCE TO GET OUT.

02:54.340 --> 02:55.842
AND YOU DIDN'T.

02:56.092 --> 02:58.720
SO NOW IT'S ON... BUMBLEBEES.

02:58.970 --> 03:00.471
{\an3}[ROARS]

02:58.970 --> 03:00.471
[PORTIA SCREAMS]

03:00.555 --> 03:02.223
[SCREAMS]

03:06.853 --> 03:09.063
Lifeguard: OH, PERFECT.

03:09.147 --> 03:10.565
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

03:10.815 --> 03:12.901
THINGS ARE GETTING TOO HEATED.

03:13.151 --> 03:14.944
ALL RIGHT, FIRST THING
WE NEED TO DO IS FIX MY RAFT.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.863
THE POOL IS BIG ENOUGH
FOR ALL OF US.

03:17.113 --> 03:18.907
OK, THE BEES SWIM FOR
FIVE MINUTES

03:19.157 --> 03:20.366
AND THEN THE FLIES SWIM FOR
FIVE MINUTES

03:20.617 --> 03:22.327
AND THEN WE HAVE A MIX SWIM.

03:22.577 --> 03:23.912
SO EVERYBODY JUST
TAKES THEIR TURN, OK?

03:24.162 --> 03:24.495
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

03:26.664 --> 03:29.125
[COUGHING AND SPUTTERING]

03:29.208 --> 03:32.795
{\an5}YOU, YOU, YOU, YOU, YOU,
YOU, YOU, YOU, YOU, YOU,
YOU-YOU-YOU-YOU AND YOU.

03:33.046 --> 03:34.213
OUT OF HERE, ALL OF YOU!

03:36.049 --> 03:37.842
THIS AIN'T OVER, BEES.

03:38.092 --> 03:39.260
{\an3}AND NEXT TIME,
WE WON'T BE SO NICE.

03:39.510 --> 03:41.346
[GASPING]

03:41.596 --> 03:44.682
[SHRIEKING]

03:46.976 --> 03:47.602
HUH?

03:50.897 --> 03:53.816
WHO WERE THOSE GIRLS?

03:54.067 --> 03:56.819
Bessie: THE OAKLAND DRAGONFLIES

03:57.070 --> 04:00.990
{\an5}ARE THE FIERCEST,
MOST NOTORIOUS GIRL TROOP
IN THE BAY AREA.

04:01.282 --> 04:03.534
EVEN THEIR PARENTS
ARE SCARED OF THEM.

04:03.785 --> 04:06.829
THEY HAVE A HISTORY OF MOVING
INTO ANOTHER TROOP'S TURF

04:07.080 --> 04:08.998
AND TAKING IT OVER.

04:09.082 --> 04:10.291
FIRST, IT WAS THE JUNE BUGS.

04:10.541 --> 04:12.919
[BICYCLE BELL RINGS]

04:13.169 --> 04:14.087
{\an5}Bessie: THE FLIES
LAUNCHED A SURPRISE ATTACK
DURING SNACK.

04:14.337 --> 04:15.505
[SCREAMING]

04:15.588 --> 04:16.505
[GRUNTS]

04:21.219 --> 04:22.262
{\an1}[COUGHING]

04:22.512 --> 04:24.514
THEN IT WAS THE BEAVERS.

04:28.476 --> 04:29.477
[GRUNTS AND GASPS]

04:32.522 --> 04:33.106
[GASPING]

04:35.233 --> 04:37.819
[SCREAMING]

04:38.069 --> 04:40.113
[CRYING]

04:40.446 --> 04:43.074
Bessie: THEIR GREATEST SHAME.

04:43.157 --> 04:46.202
LAST MONTH, THEY AMBUSHED
THE BERKELEY BUTTERFLIES

04:46.286 --> 04:48.204
DURING THEIR
ANNUAL MAYPOLE CELEBRATION.

04:48.287 --> 04:50.206
[LAUGHTER]

04:50.289 --> 04:51.290
[BICYCLE BELL DINGS]

04:51.541 --> 04:55.670
[♪...]

04:58.256 --> 05:02.677
[BUZZING]

05:02.927 --> 05:04.220
[SCREAMING]

05:04.303 --> 05:07.974
[BUZZING]

05:10.226 --> 05:13.896
[GASPS] HEY, WE WERE HAVING
NICE, CLEAN FUN, COME ON.

05:14.147 --> 05:16.441
CAN'T WE RAP ABOUT THIS?

05:16.691 --> 05:19.152
{\an5}Bessie: LEGEND HAS IT
THAT EACH DRAGONFLY
IS HANDPICKED AT BIRTH

05:19.485 --> 05:22.322
AND TRAINED IN 64 DIFFERENT
KINDS OF HAND-TO-HAND COMBAT.

05:38.671 --> 05:42.133
[ROARING]

05:42.216 --> 05:43.760
[WHINES]

05:44.010 --> 05:47.597
Bessie: PLUS, LONG DIVISION.

05:47.847 --> 05:50.475
LOOKS LIKE THEY'RE ON
THE WARPATH ONCE AGAIN.

05:50.725 --> 05:53.061
{\an1}BUT WHAT DO I KNOW, I'M SURE
THIS WILL ALL BLOW OVER.

05:53.311 --> 05:53.603
[PENNY GROANS]

05:58.775 --> 06:01.277
[GRUNTS]

06:01.360 --> 06:02.236
HEY, THE DOOR'S...

06:02.487 --> 06:02.528
[GRUNTS]

06:05.656 --> 06:07.283
[MUMBLES]

06:07.533 --> 06:09.577
[SCREAMING]

06:09.827 --> 06:11.662
WE DON'T WANT ANY.

06:11.746 --> 06:13.081
SEE YOU.

06:13.331 --> 06:16.876
[SCOFFS] WHOA, CHERRY.

06:17.126 --> 06:19.170
THIS IS, LIKE, WAY,
WAY-WAY-WAY...

06:19.253 --> 06:22.632
WAY, WAY-WAY-WAY,
WAY-WAY-WAY-WAY-WAY OFF LIMITS.

06:22.882 --> 06:25.218
UM, EXCUSE ME, UM, CHERRY?

06:25.510 --> 06:27.845
IT IS CHERRY, ISN'T IT?

06:28.096 --> 06:29.972
DULY NOTED.

06:30.389 --> 06:32.600
UM, UH, THERE APPEARS TO BE A
CASE OF CONFUSED LOCATION HERE.

06:32.850 --> 06:35.561
I'M SURE YOU DIDN'T REALIZE
THAT THIS IS OUR MEETING ROOM

06:35.812 --> 06:38.981
{\an5}WHERE HONEYBEES HAVE BEEN
HAVING MEETINGS FOR OVER,
LIKE, 30 YEARS.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.484
UM, AND WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO
ASK YOU, [GULPS]

06:41.567 --> 06:43.778
VERY POLITELY AND RESPECTFULLY,
OF COURSE

06:44.028 --> 06:46.155
UH, ASK YOU AND THE OTHER
DRAGONFLIES TO, UM...

06:46.239 --> 06:50.326
LEAVE, AWAY, NOW, G-O, OK?

06:50.409 --> 06:51.452
OK.

06:51.536 --> 06:52.620
OK?

06:52.703 --> 06:53.871
OK.

06:54.122 --> 06:55.206
MM... NO-KAY.

06:55.289 --> 06:57.125
SO THAT'S AN OK?

06:57.375 --> 06:58.292
IT'S A NO-KAY.

07:00.253 --> 07:01.796
AS IN THIS IS
DRAGONFLY TERRITORY NOW.

07:02.046 --> 07:05.174
AS IN YOUR SHOES ARE UNTIED.

07:06.801 --> 07:08.219
{\an1}THANK YOU.

07:08.302 --> 07:09.554
[CAR ZOOMS]

07:09.804 --> 07:12.348
[BRAKES SCREECH]

07:12.431 --> 07:16.060
YOU ARE ABOUT TO GET SO BUSTED.

07:16.310 --> 07:18.020
[SCOFFS] MOMMY.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.815
{\an3}Bessie: MRS. GIBBONS,
MRS. GIBBONS.

07:21.065 --> 07:23.359
{\an6}THESE DRAGONFLIES CLAIM THAT
THEY RESERVED THE MEETING ROOM,
WHICH IS IMPOSSIBLE

07:23.442 --> 07:25.862
BECAUSE WE ALWAYS MEET IN
THE HONEYBEE MEETING ROOM

07:26.112 --> 07:29.949
{\an5}AND YOU ALWAYS RENEW
THE HONEYBEE RESERVATION
EVERY MONTH, CORRECT?

07:32.285 --> 07:34.871
YOU GIRLS WORK IT OUT.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.831
[CAT SCREECHES]

07:41.002 --> 07:43.087
Woman: SO LET ME
GET THIS STRAIGHT.

07:43.337 --> 07:45.131
YOU WANT ME JUST TO ERASE
THEIR NAMES FROM THE SCHEDULE

07:45.506 --> 07:47.091
AND PUT THE HONEYBEES BACK IN?

07:47.341 --> 07:49.302
TOTES, NICE ONE, COUSIN CHELSEA.

07:49.552 --> 07:51.387
WATCH IT, PORTIA.

07:51.679 --> 07:53.931
WHEN I WEAR THIS WHISTLE,
I AM NOBODY'S COUSIN, OK?

07:54.182 --> 07:56.976
I AM THE ASSISTANT
SUMMER INTERN OF COORDINATING

07:57.226 --> 08:00.313
FOR THE SAN FRANCISCO DEPARTMENT
OF PARKS AND RECREATION.

08:00.605 --> 08:03.816
{\an1}PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE
NOT-COUSIN CHELSEA.

08:04.066 --> 08:07.028
{\an1}PLEASE, PLEASE, THERE
MUST BE SOMETHING YOU CAN DO.

08:07.278 --> 08:09.614
{\an5}PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.741
GLASSES, SHUT!

08:11.991 --> 08:13.659
PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE,
[INHALES DEEPLY]

08:13.910 --> 08:15.578
{\an1}PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE...

08:15.828 --> 08:17.121
HMM... [CLICKS TONGUE]
DON'T KNOW.

08:17.371 --> 08:20.082
DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.

08:20.333 --> 08:23.211
WELL... THERE IS ONE THING.

08:23.544 --> 08:26.422
HOLD UP, WE WERE HERE FIRST.

08:26.505 --> 08:28.007
{\an1}[SHOUTS]: YOU WANT TO
SETTLE THIS OR NOT?

08:28.257 --> 08:30.509
THOUGHT SO.

08:30.760 --> 08:34.304
PACK UP YOUR PACIFIERS AND
GET READY TO PLAY A LITTLE GAME.

08:34.388 --> 08:35.932
I'LL CALL IT...

08:36.182 --> 08:37.642
THE CHELSEA CHALLENGE.

08:40.352 --> 08:43.356
RAILROAD TRACKS, DAWN,<i> MY</i> RULES.

08:43.648 --> 08:45.524
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

08:45.775 --> 08:47.360
Chelsea: THE GOAL OF
THE CHELSEA CHALLENGE?

08:47.652 --> 08:50.363
TO MAKE <i> ME</i> HAPPY.

08:50.613 --> 08:55.243
[BEEPING]

08:55.534 --> 08:59.163
{\an5}THE WINNING TROOP
GETS AN INFINITY RESERVATION
FOR THE MEETING ROOM.

08:59.413 --> 09:02.458
THE LOSERS, [CHUCKLES],
GET TO BE LOSERS.

09:02.541 --> 09:03.834
{\an3}[RINGING]

09:04.085 --> 09:06.379
[WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY]

09:09.507 --> 09:10.591
[MOUTHING SILENTLY]

09:15.471 --> 09:18.266
[MOUTHING SILENTLY]

09:18.516 --> 09:23.312
[PHONES RINGING]

09:23.396 --> 09:26.524
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

09:46.836 --> 09:48.379
SILENCE, PLEBEIANS!

09:48.671 --> 09:51.340
[MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

09:51.674 --> 09:56.345
THE MOMENT OF TRUTH HAS ARRIVED.

09:56.679 --> 10:00.182
ONLY ONE TROOP CAN WIN
POSSESSION OF THE MEETING ROOM.

10:00.433 --> 10:02.143
WHO WILL IT BE?

10:02.393 --> 10:04.603
THE TROOP OF RECORD,
THE HONEYBEES?

10:04.854 --> 10:11.402
[CHEERING]

10:11.694 --> 10:13.195
<i>OR</i> MY OLD TROOP.

10:13.446 --> 10:14.363
[GASPING]

10:14.613 --> 10:17.158
THE DRAGONFLIES.

10:17.408 --> 10:20.328
[SCREAMING]

10:20.578 --> 10:23.873
[BICYCLE BELL RINGING]

10:24.123 --> 10:26.834
OH, AND LET'S LEVEL
THIS PLAYING FIELD.

10:27.084 --> 10:30.546
NO BIKES, BLADES,
SKATEBOARDS OR STROLLERS.

10:30.629 --> 10:32.798
[GRUNTING]

10:33.049 --> 10:35.634
I'LL GIVE YOU A BUNCH OF CLUES

10:35.885 --> 10:37.470
WHICH WILL LEAD YOU TO...

10:37.720 --> 10:39.764
THE TREASURE.

10:40.014 --> 10:41.766
{\an5}Bessie: UM, UM, EXCUSE ME?

10:40.014 --> 10:41.766
[NEEDLE SCRATCHES OFF RECORD]

10:42.099 --> 10:44.769
COUSIN CHELSEA,
WHEN YOU SAY "TREASURE"

10:45.019 --> 10:46.687
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT
SOMETHING SPECIFIC, OR...

10:46.937 --> 10:49.398
YOU'LL KNOW THE TREASURE
WHEN YOU SEE IT.

10:49.482 --> 10:50.983
AND YOU'LL BRING IT TO ME.

10:51.233 --> 10:53.486
ON ALCATRAZ.

10:53.778 --> 10:55.571
[CROWD GASPING]

10:55.863 --> 10:57.573
FIRST TROOP TO DELIVER
THE GOODS WINS.

10:57.865 --> 10:59.658
YOUR MISSION STARTS NOW!

10:59.909 --> 11:01.285
CATCH A CLUE.

11:01.535 --> 11:02.870
[SCOFFS] I DON'T CATCH.

11:06.665 --> 11:10.544
[SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

11:10.628 --> 11:11.587
Penny: GUM-GUM-GUM-GUM-GUM.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.054
[BARKS]

11:20.304 --> 11:22.181
[BARKS AND GROWLS]

11:22.431 --> 11:23.808
THEY'RE GONE, YOU GUYS, COME ON.

11:27.645 --> 11:30.064
[♪...]

11:30.314 --> 11:32.024
Bessie: "HEAD SOUTH.

11:32.274 --> 11:33.984
"FIND THE FARM WHERE
NOTHING GROWS.

11:34.235 --> 11:35.611
"THE CLUE IS THERE.

11:35.694 --> 11:37.279
MAKE SURE YOU MARK IT."

11:41.117 --> 11:42.618
[GRUNTS]

11:42.701 --> 11:44.829
Cherry: AH, THE FARMERS MARKET.

12:00.719 --> 12:02.555
[HOWLS]

12:02.847 --> 12:04.348
ATTABOY, AFTER 'EM.

12:04.598 --> 12:06.142
RUN LIKE THE WIND.

12:10.855 --> 12:11.480
[WHISTLES]

12:17.194 --> 12:18.863
Girl: "GO-GO'S FRO-YO"?

12:19.113 --> 12:20.948
{\an1}OH, OH, I'VE BEEN THERE,
I'VE BEEN THERE.

12:21.198 --> 12:21.949
COME ON, GIRLS.

12:28.747 --> 12:31.417
[HOWLS]

12:34.712 --> 12:36.964
GREAT, EMPTY, OF COURSE.

12:37.214 --> 12:39.675
{\an1}COME ON, GWEN, YOU CAN'T
LOOK AT IT LIKE THAT.

12:39.925 --> 12:41.093
WE CAN DO THIS.

12:41.343 --> 12:42.636
HONEYBEE, PLEASE.

12:42.720 --> 12:44.096
Portia: SERIOUSLY.

12:44.346 --> 12:45.514
I'M READY TO BLOW THIS OFF.

12:45.806 --> 12:47.892
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

12:48.142 --> 12:50.478
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
THE FATE OF THE HONEYBEES HERE.

12:50.728 --> 12:53.355
YAWN.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.649
{\an6}BESSIE, UH, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT TIME WE'RE GOING TO BE
DONE FIGHTING FOR OUR FUTURE?

12:55.733 --> 12:59.403
VICTORY TIME, THAT'S WHEN.

12:59.653 --> 13:01.530
{\an1}YOU GUYS, ALL WE
HAVE TO DO IS WORK TOGETHER.

13:01.614 --> 13:03.240
[SCOFFS] SOUND AWESOME.

13:03.491 --> 13:05.242
EXCEPT FOR THE WORK PART.

13:05.493 --> 13:06.660
AND, OH, YEAH,
THE TOGETHER PART, TOO.

13:06.994 --> 13:10.247
IS THERE GONNA BE A SNACK TODAY?

13:13.584 --> 13:17.171
UGH, WHY DON'T YOU GUYS,
JUST... JUST...

13:17.421 --> 13:19.215
<i>BUZZ OFF?</i>

13:19.465 --> 13:20.424
[GASPING]

13:20.674 --> 13:21.592
[GASPING]

13:21.675 --> 13:22.927
[GASPING]

13:23.177 --> 13:24.720
BESSIE, PLEASE.

13:32.102 --> 13:35.105
WHATEVER, WHO NEEDS HER, ANYWAY?

13:35.356 --> 13:36.982
WAIT A SEC'.

13:37.233 --> 13:39.527
[SNIFFS] I KNOW
WHAT WAS IN HERE.

13:39.777 --> 13:41.529
CHELSEA'S FAVE-FAVE.

13:41.779 --> 13:44.532
STRAWBERRY FROZEN YOGURT.

13:44.865 --> 13:47.743
I KNOW WHERE
THOSE GRODY FLIES WENT.

13:47.826 --> 13:49.245
PIER 31.

13:49.495 --> 13:50.746
I THOUGHT WE DIDN'T CARE.

13:50.829 --> 13:52.915
WE DON'T, OBVIOUSLY.

13:53.165 --> 13:55.167
BUT DO YOU WANNA LOSE TO
SOMEONE NAMED CHERRY?

13:55.417 --> 13:58.003
AND I DON'T WANNA
LET THE BEES DOWN OR WHATEVER.

13:58.254 --> 14:00.172
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

14:00.422 --> 14:01.799
{\an5}NO TOUCH.

14:00.422 --> 14:01.799
{\an1}SORRY, OK.

14:02.132 --> 14:04.718
SO WHAT, WE'RE GONNA DO THIS?

14:04.802 --> 14:06.220
{\an1}I GUESS.

14:06.470 --> 14:08.764
THEN WHAT NEED ARE <i> WHEELS.</i>

14:08.847 --> 14:10.849
[♪...]

14:11.100 --> 14:14.186
CHELSEA DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT ROLLER SKATES.

14:14.436 --> 14:19.775
♪ WE ARE THE HONEYBEES
AND WE ARE HERE TO STAY ♪

14:19.858 --> 14:22.903
♪ NO DRAGONFLY COULD EVER
SHOO US AWAY ♪

14:23.153 --> 14:25.781
♪ YEAH, YEAH-YEAH-YEAH,
